# 🚀 P99Soft Portfolio Website - Backend

This is the backend of the **P99Soft Pvt. Ltd. Portfolio Website**, responsible for handling contact form submissions and sending emails using Nodemailer.

---

## 🛠️ Tech Stack

* 🟢 Node.js
* 🚂 Express.js
* 📧 Nodemailer
* 🔐 dotenv (Environment Variables)
* 🌐 CORS

---

## 📂 Project Structure

```
backend/
│── node_modules/
│── .env
│── server.js
│── package.json
```

---

## ✨ Features

* 📩 Send emails from contact form
* 🔐 Secure environment variable handling
* 🌍 CORS enabled for frontend integration
* ⚡ Lightweight and fast server

---

## ⚙️ Installation & Setup

### 1️⃣ Clone the repository

```bash
git clone https://github.com/your-username/p99soft-portfolio.git
cd backend
```

### 2️⃣ Install dependencies

```bash
npm install
```

### 3️⃣ Setup environment variables

Create a `.env` file:

```
PORT=5000

EMAIL_USER=your-email@gmail.com
EMAIL_PASS=your-app-password
```

⚠️ Use **App Password** (not your real Gmail password)

---

## ▶️ Run the server

```bash
node server.js
```

OR (if using nodemon)

```bash
npx nodemon server.js
```

---

## 📡 API Endpoints

### 📩 Send Email

```
POST /send-email
```

### Request Body:

```json
{
  "name": "John Doe",
  "email": "john@example.com",
  "message": "Hello, I am interested in your services."
}
```

---

## 🔐 Security Notes

* Never expose `.env` file
* Use app passwords for email
* Add rate limiting in production

